@SiteEffect (did you change your name), thanks for the effort, but the complications are more than that. What if the text contains special characters (e.g. `>`, `<`, `&` in HTML, `_`, `*` in Markdown)? After applying the entities to the string, the user should reasonably expect that all special characters are also properly escaped. 

Escaping them *before* applying entities may screw up the offsets. Escaping them *after* applying entities is hard because you got a lot more special characters mixed in. If you want a function to apply entities in a reasonable way, that function should also take care of escaping special characters properly.

Given all that extra work, I would prefer the entity-applying function to be in a separate module. I am thinking of implementing that myself. It's up to you if you want to go ahead yourself. :smile: Thanks anyway.

