重复发一个TCP会话的数据，IV是曾经用过的。OTA是单向到服务器的，不能由服务器告诉客户端时间戳，那么OTA上行包里加上时间戳也是个办法，同时服务器应该缓存起近期用过的IV，不充许同一个近期IV再发起请求。

另外，如果把时间戳和IV关联起来，比如每个IV由当时的时间戳通过某种算法生成，通过逆算法用密码和IV可以反解出时间戳，服务端不就也可以对IV进行合法性检验？

With `Path` property of `Events` structure, SAM needs to insert the value of this property into Swagger as a key of a dictionary like this:

```
{
  "paths": {
     "<Value of Path property>": {...}
  }
}
```

Since SAM runs "before" any intrinsic functions are processed, it has no way of getting the path string that you expect to be obtained by resolving the intrinsics. SAM works around this problem in most cases by carefully passing the value (containing intrinsics) directly to the next stage of processing that deploys the stack. In case of Path, we need cannot insert an intrinsic function as a key of a dictionary. Therefore SAM gives up and fails. Policies, on the other hand, are never entirely resolved in SAM. They are passed through directly to the next layer if SAM finds an intrinsic function there.

Ah yes, I didn't take into account the `nonGapMismatchCount`, which shouldn't count non-matched ambiguous bases as mismatches. `nonGapMismatchCount`should count if there is a non-ambiguous mismatch or if `matchAmbiguous`is True. 

Could this be a solution?
```
if len(AMBIGUOUS[b]) > 1:
        read2AmbiguousOffsets.append(offset)
if a == b and len(AMBIGUOUS[a]) == 1:
        identicalMatchCount += 1
elif len(AMBIGUOUS[a]) == 1 and len(AMBIGUOUS[b]) == 1:
        nonGapMismatchCount += 1
elif matchAmbiguous:
        if AMBIGUOUS.get(a, empty) & AMBIGUOUS.get(b, empty):
                  ambiguousMatchCount += 1
        else:
                  nonGapMismatchCount += 1
```

As to the issue that I was working on, in #573 the title and the actual text in the issue seem two adress different things to me (title: make matchAmbiguous more stringent; text: allow identicalMatchCount only to count identical non-ambiguos matches). So I would leave in my changes in 
```
if a == b and len(AMBIGUOUS[a]) == 1:
       identicalMatchCount += 1
```
as well, as it fixes the issue adressed in the #573 text.

@marwoodandrew how do you store bytes in database ? formatted_item is flagged as string, so I guess binary data should cause troubles. In any case, I think it's a bad thing to have different behavior with transmitters (i.e. file_output handling bytes or str, and not the others).

@petrjasek wanted to keep unicode, because binary would make preview harder

An option to handle this may be to have 2 values: formatted_item for str, or encoded_item for bytes.
If the formatter wishes to produce byte it create encoded_item itself, in addition to formatted_item.
If not it can give formatted_item with on optional encoding (which default to "utf-8").

This way I think we can keep best of 2 options: we have unicode for previewing, and bytes for binary data.

